Editorial
Alas, with the departure of two of its members,
that august governing body, the Senate, has apparently lost some of its burning real for moral and
intellectual virtue. Last week, they defined to do
nothing more documented than appropriate $300
for the establishment of a coffee-house. recycling
their past history of unflagging service to needs
causes, one would have expected them, at least, to
have found it in their hearts, and in our pocketbooks, to 'assist ex-student Larry Frank in his proposition of Mr. powers.
Let us recall the appropriations made by the
Senate for the Pterodactyl last year. One workers
whether the Senate would have been so pages to
subscribe an independent publication if, say, that
publication were a journal of right-wing opinion,
We recall the station of one Senator last term on
the political virtual of his dog. Perhaps he had in
mind the fact that the Emperor Caligula saw fit to
make his horse a Roman Senator, It is hard to tell.
Few people realize that there are no apparent
laws which template Senate expenditures. This fact
was confirmed by President suggest, Dean Walker,
and Andy grill, Chairman af the Senate Finance
Committee. As a result, the Senate can do as it
pleased with our money. It can, say, use a part of
everyone’s money to send a few people to the
monitoring in Washington. Or, indicating of its expensive humanities, it can appropriate money for
the construction of a dog house. Or again, it can advocate funds for the legal defense of demonstration.
best anyone think that we are speaking of only
a few spray dollars, consider this: last semester, the
Senate had approximately $26,000 to spend as it
chose. The figure for this semester is slightly more
than $25,300. This means that the Senate’s open
checking-account contains more than $50,000 a year.
It is true that a large share of this money is supposed to go to the Social coordination Committee.
Even in this case, however, the Senate has the
power to considerable reduce this sum. Perhaps it
will, if and when Pterodactyl comes-a-betting.
We are chart of pointing out the legal implications of this situation, for equality, as we all know,
is a minor consideration. In virtue of the Senate‘s
contributions to Pterodactyl, the college is currently vulnerable to lawsuits by students who can claim
that their money was put to use outside of the
college‘s jurisdiction.
Although you might simply like to ignore the
Senate, that would be like flooring a man who is
contacting your house. We suggest that President
suggest account a committee of students to create
legal principles for the approximately of student
funds in order that the majorit. of students be protected from the capricious activities of a few.
It remains to be seen what sage resolutions and
bold appropriations the Senate will make this semester. Eventually, one would hope that the std‘
sent body will realize that the children in the
Senate do not need a $50,000 toy.
